{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN1/mahaddhana-sutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>“The affluent and the wealthy, <br>\neven the aristocrats who rule the land, <br>\nare jealous of each other, <br>\ninsatiable in sensual pleasures. <br>\n<br>\nAmong those of such an avid nature, <br>\nflowing along the stream of lives, <br>\nwho here has given up craving? <br>\nWho in the world is not avid?” <br>\n<br>\n“Having given up their home, their child, their cattle, <br>\nand all that they love, they went forth. <br>\nHaving given up desire and hate, <br>\nhaving dispelled ignorance, <br>\nthe perfected ones with defilements ended— <br>\nthey in the world are not avid.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN1/catucakka-sutta/\">SN.1.29. Catucakka Sutta (“Four Wheels”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“The affluent and the wealthy, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\neven the aristocrats who rule the land, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nare jealous of each other, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\ninsatiable in sensual pleasures. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nAmong those of such an avid nature, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nflowing along the stream of lives, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","proper